# Multi-Agent Boundaries

## Service Ownership (DO NOT cross)

| Service | Path | Owns | Must NOT implement |
|---------|------|------|--------------------|
| Control Service | `apps/server` | Users, profiles, workflows, orchestration, monitoring | Board scraping, browser automation |
| Job Fetcher | `packages/jobs_scraper` | Board adapters, fetch execution, normalization, dedupe | User CRUD, application logic |
| Job Applier | `packages/jobs_applier` | Browser automation, form filling, step traces | User CRUD, matching, fetching |
| Frontend | `apps/client` | UI, forms, dashboards, monitoring views | Backend business logic |

## Rules

1. **Contracts first** — Shared DTOs, status enums, event schemas before feature work
2. **No duplicate ownership** — Consume contracts, do not re-implement across services
3. **Tenant-aware** — All major models scoped by tenant
4. **Resumability & idempotency** — Design for durable, resumable workflows
5. **Small tasks** — One endpoint, one model, one component per change
